'''Kevin Danso''' (born 19 September 1998) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

Formerly a youth international at various levels from under-15 to [[Austria national under-21 football team|under-21]], Danso made his debut for the Austria senior team in 2017.

==Early life==
Danso was born in Austria to Ghanaian parents before moving to [[Milton Keynes]] in England at the age of six.<ref name="tribalfootball">{{cite web|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/england-scouts-urged-to-check-augsburg-whizkid-kevin-danso-4172028|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309215347/http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/england-scouts-urged-to-check-augsburg-whizkid-kevin-danso-4172028|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 March 2017|title=England scouts urged to check Augsburg whizkid Kevin Danso|work=tribalfootball.com}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Early years===
Danso joined the academy of [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]] at under 9 level having previously been a striker in the [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] academy,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/fc-augsburg/kevin-danso-liess-england-karriere-sausen-50747314.bild.html |title=Danso ließ England-Karriere sausen |work=Bild |date=7 March 2017 |accessdate=27 February 2018 }}</ref><ref name="tribalfootball" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/11266682/jadon-sancho-ademola-lookman-why-premier-league-youngsters-are-choosing-the-bundesliga |title=Jadon Sancho, Ademola Lookman: Why Premier League youngsters are choosing the Bundesliga |publisher=Sky Sports |date=27 February 2018 |accessdate=27 February 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/kevin-danso-augsburg-wonderkid-dele-alli-mk-dons-desailly-474586.jsp |title=Kevin Danso: Alli's friend, Batshuayi's foe, Augsburg's Austrian wonderkid |work=bundesliga.com |accessdate=26 July 2020 |archive-date=10 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210032527/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/kevin-danso-augsburg-wonderkid-dele-alli-mk-dons-desailly-474586.jsp |url-status=dead }}</ref> staying at the club until 2014 before moving to [[FC Augsburg]] in Germany.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://football-wonderkids.co.uk/player/kevin-danso/ |title=Kevin Danso |website=football-wonderkids.co.uk |access-date=6 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Frimpong |first=El Akyereko |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/kevin-danso-austria-u17-coach-says-ghanaian-midfielder-is-irreplaceable-in-his-squad |title=Kevin Danso: Austria U17 coach says Ghanaian midfielder is irreplaceable in his squad |website=Ghanasoccernet |date=9 May 2015 |access-date=27 February 2018}}</ref>

===FC Augsburg===
On 3 March 2017, Danso made his [[Bundesliga]] debut for [[FC Augsburg]] at the age of 18 years and 165 days old, becoming the youngest player to make a league appearance in the club's history.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Langner|first1=Wolfgang|title=Kevin Danso ist nach seinem Debüt ein gefragter Mann|url=https://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fc-augsburg/Kevin-Danso-ist-nach-seinem-Debuet-ein-gefragter-Mann-id40780891.html|accessdate=24 May 2017|work=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=4 March 2017|language=German}}</ref><ref name="nt">{{cite news|title=Baum über Danso: "Es ist eine Sensation"|url=https://www.kicker.de/baum-ueber-danso_es-ist-eine-sensation-678817/artikel|access-date=24 May 2017|date=24 May 2017|language=German}}</ref> A week later, he signed a new four-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Yeboah|first1=Thomas Freeman|title=Ghanaian youngster signs 4-year deal with Bundesliga side Augsburg|url=http://pulse.com.gh/sports/kevin-danso-ghanaian-youngster-signs-4-year-deal-with-bundesliga-side-augsburg-id6348394.html|accessdate=24 May 2017|work=Pulse Ghana|date=10 March 2017|archive-date=15 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315090142/http://pulse.com.gh/sports/kevin-danso-ghanaian-youngster-signs-4-year-deal-with-bundesliga-side-augsburg-id6348394.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Southampton loan====
On 9 August 2019, the day after the [[Premier League]] [[transfer window]] closed, it was announced that Danso signed for [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] on a one-year loan, with the option to buy at the end of the [[2019–20 Premier League|2019–20 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49290375 |title=Kevin Danso: Southampton sign defender on loan from Augsburg |work=BBC Sport |date=9 August 2019 |accessdate=26 July 2020 }}</ref>

====Fortuna Düsseldorf loan====
On 18 August 2020 he went to [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web|title=FCA verleiht Kevin Danso nach Düsseldorf|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/de/article/fca-verleiht-kevin-danso-nach-duesseldorf-11863|access-date=19 August 2020|website=FC Augsburg|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Fortuna leiht Innenverteidiger Kevin Danso aus|url=https://www.f95.de/aktuell/news/profis/detail/25949-fortuna-leiht-innenverteidiger-kevin-danso-aus/c6e41d2ee784fb64da14425a3a7d2e01/|access-date=19 August 2020|website=Fortuna Düsseldorf 1895|language=de}}</ref> He left Fortuna upon the expiration of his contract on 24 May 2021.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Fortuna Düsseldorf]]|url=https://www.f95.de/aktuell/news/profis/detail/27358-saisonausklang-im-kreise-der-mannschaft/133bdcfb528c157547d4c85ef6e037ff/|title=SAISONAUSKLANG IM KREISE DER MANNSCHAFT|date=24 May 2021|language=de}}</ref>

===Lens===
On 6 August 2021, Danso joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[RC Lens]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/mercato-contrat-kevin-danso-rclens-20210806|title=Kevin Danso, de la puissance en defense !|date=6 August 2021|accessdate=6 August 2021|language=fr}}</ref> On 19 March 2022, he scored his first goal with Lens against [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/03/19/france/ligue-1/racing-club-de-lens/clermont-foot-auvergne/3526184/|title=Lens vs. Clermont|website=Soccerway|access-date=19 March 2022}}</ref> During the [[2022–23 Ligue 1|2022–23 season]], he played a crucial role in helping his team secure second place in the league and qualify for the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|following season's Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Riley |first=Martha |url=https://talksport.com/football/1911382/kevin-danso-rio-ferdinand-euro-2024-austria-manchester-united/ |title=Kevin Danso had tough time at Southampton but Rio Ferdinand has tipped Austria Euro 2024 star for Manchester United rebuild |publisher=talkSPORT |date=17 June 2024 }}</ref>

===Tottenham Hotspur===
On 2 February 2025, Danso joined [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on loan for the remainder of [[2024–25 Premier League|the season]] with an obligation to buy at the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 February 2025 |title=Tottenham sign Kevin Danso from Lens to boost injury hit squad |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/43655423/tottenham-sign-kevin-danso-lens-boost-injury-hit-squad |access-date=2 February 2025 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> He made his first appearance for Spurs on 6 February in a 4–0 defeat away to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[2024–25 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] semi-final.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Anderson |first1=Jess |title=Liverpool 4 Tottenham Hotspur 0 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn8y2xv4ygqt |access-date=7 February 2025 |work=BBC Sport |date=6 February 2025}}</ref> Danso was selected in the squad that played the [[2025 UEFA Europa League final]], entering the game as a substitute, and helping Tottenham to win their first trophy for seventeen years.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stone |first1=Simon |title=UEFA Europa League Final: Tottenham 1–0 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cz9yney9391t |website=BBC Sport |access-date=22 May 2025 |date=21 May 2025}}</ref>

On 31 May 2025, Danso joined Tottenham Hotspur permanently from Lens for £21&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Player update – Tottenham Hotspur|date=31 May 2025|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/may/player-update/|access-date=31 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Brotherton|first=Alex|title=Spurs complete £21m Kevin Danso signing from Lens – BBC Sport|date=31 May 2025|website=bbc.co.uk/sport/|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cg4veevwyddo|access-date=31 May 2025}}</ref>

Danso started in the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup]], playing the full match against PSG as Tottenham lost on penalties after the match ended 2–2.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG vs Tottenham LIVE: European Champions beat Spurs on penalties to win Super Cup |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cjr1l8epz02t |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Danso was used as a long throw-in specialist in the match, drawing significant media attention.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tweedale |first=Ali |date=2025-08-23 |title=Are Long Throw-ins Back in the Premier League? |url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/long-throw-ins-premier-league-stats |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=Opta Analyst |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Allnutt |first=Tom |date=2025-08-22 |title=Tottenham’s new long-throw specialist who grew up idolising Jackie Chan |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/tottenham-hotspur-kevin-danso-long-throw-3lhr8j2cv |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=www.thetimes.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Kevin Danso on long throw-ins and battling with Haaland: exclusive interview – all the latest news today – 112.ua |url=https://112.ua/en/kevin-danso-wanted-to-be-action-movie-star-as-a-kid-now-tottenham-star-ready-to-unleash-lethal-weapon-at-man-city-80022 |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=112.ua |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Austria national under-21 football team - Teamcamp October 2019 (35).jpg|thumb|230x230px|Danso with [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria U21]] in 2019]]
Danso was eligible to represent Ghana or Austria internationally.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/england-scouts-urged-to-check-augsburg-whizkid-kevin-danso-1488965491 |title=England handlers to swoop for Augsburg's Ghanaian whizkid Kevin Danso |publisher=GhanaSoccernet |date=8 March 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Youngster-Kevin-Danso-picks-Austria-over-Ghana-452594 |title=Youngster Kevin Danso picks Austria over Ghana |work=GhanaWeb |publisher=Ghana Web |date=4 July 2016 }}</ref> He represented Austria's [[Austria national under-15 football team|U15]], [[Austria national under-16 football team|U16]], [[Austria national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Austria national under-18 football team|Austria U18]], and [[Austria national under-19 football team|U19]] youth teams.

In May 2017, he received his first call-up to the [[Austria national football team|senior national team]].<ref name="nt"/> In June 2024, he was named in the Austrian squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Nationalteam-Kader für UEFA EURO 2024 fixiert |trans-title=Final national team squad for UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/OeFB-Kader-UEFA-EURO-2024 |language=de |publisher=[[Austrian Football Association]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref>

In October 2025, he was part of “Austrian football history” as he played the entire match in a 10–0 victory over San Marino, Austria's biggest win in international football.<ref>{{cite news |date=9 October 2025 |title=Danso assist in Austria’s record win|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/october/internationals-danso-assist-in-austria-s-record-win
|language=en |publisher=[[Tottenham Hotspur]] |access-date=19 October 2025}}</ref>

